column2:
Libertador stance and moves are enhancend
Sucessful parries restore Heat meter
Gains access to LIB d+3+4 and b+2~F

column7: A bit slow, but an useful mid heat engager for pressure.

A homing heat engager. The second hit can be ducked if 
 the first one is blocked, so it's a good idea to mix it with 
 her other possible follow-ups and stance cancel.

Mostly used as a follow-up after certain moves such as 
 f,f+4 on hit, but can also be used as a situational punish 
 on moves that recover crouching.

Single jab to check situations. Its extensions are mostly 
 useful for punishment. If you want a jab string for poking 
 go for 2,1 instead.

column3:
automatically evades
high and low attacks

column7: Mid poke string with many useful follow-ups.

Low pokes to mix with your mids. db+3 shifts to BT stance 
  to create mindgames on hit and on block.

Quick counterhit launcher that has high crush properties. 
 Good to callout opponents counter poking with jab strings 
 and other high attacks.
A safe mid launcher that can jump over low attacks.

Very risky evasive attack that can help you steal turns 
 or get out of some mixup situations.

Useful to approach opponents with in the midrange. 
  Shifts to LIB (or BT by holding back). Good way to start your 
  stance offense.

Use this to approach and pressure the opponent from afar. 
  Can now shift to LIB by holding forward.

column12: (on low wallsplat)  LIB d+3 ⏵ FC df+4
df+4,1 T! ⏵ LIB d+3 ⏵ FC df+4

For a damage ender using heat burst, you can do
heat burst ⏵ f+4,4~F ⏵ db+3+4

After the tornado, you can use df+4,1 for mid distance carry
or 4,3 for a very long and high wallsplat
Use d+1 to break floors and f+1+2 or f,f,f+3,2 to wall break.
